content.text: With CSS, links can be styled in many different ways.
content.html: With CSS, links can be styled in many different ways.

content.text: Links can be styled with any CSS property (e.g. color , font-family , background , etc.).
content.html: Links can be styled with any CSS property (e.g. color, font-family, background, etc.).

content.code_html:
a {
  color: hotpink;
}

content.text: In addition, links can be styled differently depending on what state they are in.
content.html: In addition, links can be styled differently depending on what state they are in.

content.code_html:
/* unvisited link */
a:link {
  color: red;
}

/* visited link */
a:visited {
  color: green;
}

/* mouse over link */
a:hover {
  color: hotpink;
}

/* selected link */
a:active {
  color: blue;
}

content.text: The text-decoration property is mostly used to remove underlines from links:
content.html: The text-decoration property is mostly used to remove underlines from links:

content.code_html:
a:link {
  text-decoration: none;
}

a:visited {
  text-decoration: none;
}

a:hover {
  text-decoration: underline;
}

a:active {
  text-decoration: underline;
}

content.text: The background-color property can be used to specify a background color for links:
content.html: The background-color property can be used to specify a background color for links:

content.code_html:
a:link {
  background-color: yellow;
}

a:visited {
  background-color: cyan;
}

a:hover {
  background-color: lightgreen;
}

a:active {
  background-color: hotpink;
}

content.code_html:
a:link, a:visited {
  background-color: white;
  color: black;
  border: 2px solid green;
  padding: 10px 20px;
  text-align: center;
  text-decoration: none;
  display: inline-block;
}

a:hover, a:active {
  background-color: green;
  color: white;
}
